description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in a career in acute medicine? If so there is a position for a band 4 Discharge Co-ordinator to work across the medical floor to organise and facilitate discharges. We are looking for people who have previous experience of working within the trust and are familiar with the computer systems used. You will part of a team of discharge co-ordinators that rotate around the medical floor, and to be the single point of access whilst on duty for all discharges within the area of responsibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are one of the largest acute Trusts in England and are in the enviable position of being surrounded by beautiful beaches and the Kent countryside but with easy links to the centre of London. So, whether you are interested in cathedrals, castles, exceptional grammar schools or chic and stylish restaurants, East Kent has something for everyone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff and patients from across East Kent Hospitals (EKHUFT) are the feature of the biggest NHS recruitment drive in its 70-year history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‘We are the NHS’ campaign highlights the extraordinary work that staff across our organisation do every single day. Serving a population of over one million people, EKHUFT was perfectly placed to demonstrate the care, cutting-edge treatments, research, innovations and life-saving operations that the campaign needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lisa Turrell, Job title: Matron, Email address: lisa.turrell@nhs.net, Telephone number: 07770327099&lt;/p&gt;
